Package api

Interface node_data

All Known Implementing Classes:
NodeData
public interface node_data
This interface represents the set of operations applicable on a node (vertex) in a (directional) weighted graph.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    java.lang.String getInfo()
    Returns the remark (meta data) associated with this node.
    int getKey()
    Returns the key (id) associated with this node.
    geo_location getLocation()
    Returns the location of this node, if none return null.
    int getTag()
    Temporal data (aka color: e,g, white, gray, black) which can be used be algorithms
    double getWeight()
    Returns the weight associated with this node.
    void setInfo​(java.lang.String s)
    Allows changing the remark (meta data) associated with this node.
    void setLocation​(geo_location p)
    Allows changing this node's location.
    void setTag​(int t)
    Allows setting the "tag" value for temporal marking an node - common practice for marking by algorithms.
    void setWeight​(double w)
    Allows changing this node's weight.
